      "thesis": "While industrial consolidation transformed the American economy by concentrating unprecedented wealth and productive power in the hands of large corporations, it simultaneously generated the political and social movements — labor unions, Populism, and Progressive reform — that would ultimately force the state to impose regulatory constraints on corporate power, making the Gilded Age a period of transformation in both directions.",
